It is a bit ambiguous how you react to reviews that are less than 4 stars, and your passive aggression towards those who face unapologetic treatment and leave a 1-star review.
We don’t question anyone’s positive experience at this restaurant; we are exercising our right to share our own experience and how we were treated, to prevent further customers from spending a beautiful day/iftar during Ramadan in an unwelcoming space.
You have mentioned that you are very confused about the way we acted. Shouldn’t you be more confused that your internal communications are not well managed? We now have a situation where a representative from the restaurant is making false allegations about the reservation made for 15 people, when, in fact, it was clearly communicated as a reservation for 20 people.
Additionally, you should not use the number of guests as a shield to claim they were 'screaming.' While a group of 20 might naturally be livelier, this does not justify using the size of the group to make impolite accusations.
You need to be trained in how to constructively respond to reviews. Secondly, you should know how to approach customers with basic manners and avoid a rude attitude.
As for the food, while it was not as tasty as it would be in Turkic countries, this is a subjective view, considering my background with the original cuisine.
Sincerely hope that gaslighting your customers and respecting their right to review is not beyond you.

I want to write this review in the hope that it will encourage you to improve your service. While I appreciate your efforts, there are definitely areas that need work.

On Saturday, I called to reserve a table for 15 people for Sunday at 7 pm, as we were coming for iftar. Later, on Sunday around 3 pm, I called again to request adding 5 more people to the reservation. I noticed your response to my friends' reviews, where you complained about us exceeding 20 people and mentioned needing more time to prepare the table. Excuse me, but how much time does it really take to move and combine tables? For the record, we ended up being 21 people—just one person more than expected. As someone who has managed a Turkish restaurant before, I don’t understand why you’re complaining about having more customers. It’s not like they were dining for free. To be precise, we left a bill of around $800. Additionally, the restaurant wasn’t full—there were empty tables available.

I also saw that you mentioned us screaming, but I don’t recall anything like that happening. Everyone in our group was well-behaved and respectful.

Another issue I’d like to address is the payment process. You made it unnecessarily difficult for us, and we spent almost an hour dividing the bill. You refused to let everyone pay individually, claiming, "Everybody in Manhattan does it this way," which is simply not true. Most restaurants allow customers to pay in whatever way they prefer, especially when dealing with large groups. Instead of showing courtesy and flexibility, you were stubborn and unhelpful, which could easily lead to losing customers.

Lastly, as someone who managed a Turkish restaurant for almost a year and lived in Turkey for eight years, I have high standards for Turkish cuisine. Unfortunately, the food left me disappointed. This is my personal opinion, as I understand my expectations might be higher than others. I ordered chicken soup, which had huge pieces of onion that made it difficult to enjoy—I couldn’t finish it, and you probably remember clearing a half-full bowl. The stuffed grape leaves (dolma) were also not fresh, and I couldn’t finish those either. As for the kebabs my friends ordered, they were too dry. Again, this might be due to my high standards for Turkish food.

Here’s a tip for future reference: If you want to maintain and grow your business, focus on understanding and addressing your customers' concerns instead of making unfair judgments. Strive to improve your service and food quality to gain your customers' trust, rather than losing them.

Akdeniz Turkish restaurant in Manhattan has a beautiful ambiance and consistently fast, friendly service. I’ve visited multiple times, and while the food can be outstanding on some days, it occasionally misses the mark on others. For instance, the soup and mixed meze platter (as shown in my photos) were fresh and flavorful during one visit, but lacked the same depth of taste a few weeks later. Still, when the dishes are on point—especially the Iskender consistency, this remains my go-to Turkish spot whenever I’m in Manhattan. If you’re looking for a cozy atmosphere and hospitable staff, it’s worth checking out. Just be aware that the flavors, though often excellent, may vary from visit to visit.

reviewText: Just no. These are pre packaged battered fries that they are taking out of sealed bags and throwing in oil. They are dry on the inside and nothing like the deliciousness of Belgian fries, which are thick, made of fresh potato and mix crunch with softness properly. Aside from paying nearly 7 bucks for a small fries to have to also pay 1.25 for sauce is outrageous. Again, rather than smothering fries with delicious fresh sauce, you get a small plastic cup. Even the guy running the place didn’t break a smile once. It’s not inedible but it’s pricey and you can probably get better, fresh fries in most restaurants in the area. Such a disappointment.

This place serves fries like you’d find in the Netherlands or Europe—crispy on the outside, fluffy on the inside, and served with a huge variety of sauces. The Black Truffle Mayo is a must-try, especially with the large-size fries.

The interior has a medieval-style decor, but they play modern pop music, which is kind of a weird mix—but in a cool way.

The menu is all about their signature fries, double-fried for that perfect texture, with over 30 dipping sauces ranging from classics like roasted garlic aioli to more unique options like Vietnamese pineapple.

It’s a small spot but super popular with both locals and tourists. Great for a quick, delicious snack, and they’re open late—until midnight on weekdays and 2 AM on weekends—so perfect for late-night cravings!

The highlight here is definitely the paella. I've never been to Spain, but it was the most delicious paella I've ever had in my life. I ordered Langosta, and I recommend it. However, please note that it is for two people and that one paella costs at least $35 per person. The staff are very friendly and professional. The ambiance immediately caught my attention, and after five months of dining there, I can confidently say it’s one of my favorite restaurants in the city—if not *the* favorite. The staff is incredibly welcoming, making every visit feel like catching up with friends. And the food? Absolutely exceptional. You can tell they put real care into every dish, whether for dine-in or takeout. I’ve recommended B Cafe to my friends, many of whom are now loyal customers. In fact, I’m planning to eat there tonight!

Speaking of service, I asked about a beer list (it’s a Belgian place after all!) and was told that they didn’t have one? Turns out they do, and I had to find it online to order something that wasn’t on tap. We also had to flag her down to order another drink after we sat around for a while. The other issue was that we were sat outside in their heated backyard, but the heat was questionable and I couldn’t feel my feet by the end of it. So, over all, so so.

However, we encountered an issue with one of our orders—a medium-cooked burger that arrived rare. As a professional chef accustomed to preparing rare burgers, I found this to be undercooked. When we brought this to our server’s attention, the response was less accommodating than expected, offering only half a burger as compensation. This aspect of our experience was disappointing.

We hold your restaurant in high regard and consider ourselves friends of the establishment. Our intention in sharing this feedback is to ensure that future visits are as impeccable as possible. We look forward to returning and hope that our next experience will reflect the high standards we have come to associate with your restaurant.

Haven’t tried the food yet though. But always grab a few beers.
Sixpoint is great! If you find yourself in the Brooklyn by the food hall. Check out Sixpoint! Great food, service, beer and spirits. James was awesome behind the bar!

Great beer and service. Also a solid merch selection.

Fun part of the City Point market, right at the bottom of the stairs. Quick service and almost immediate delivery of cold apps and soup/chili. Big selection of merchandise and beer to go, too. $5 Saturday happy hour killed it.

This is my favorite brewery in NYC. They always have new freshly brewed beers on the menu and tend to be experimental when it comes to styles. I love their 2/3/4(!)X IPAs, have yet to find anything better here - and there’s a lot of other breweries. Great outdoor space and you can bring your own food. Every time I’m in the area I make sure to make a stop here.

This place is doing high level stuff. Interesting and diverse beer list with unique concepts related to everything from hops fermentation styles. Vibe is great and the staff is super nice. Can’t recommend enough.

We were altered to this new-ish brewery when we stopped by another brewery around the corner during a craft beer 'crawl'. WOW! Glad we did. An amazing space which includes a huge covered area (great for large parties). They also have a patio out back.

The beer. Mostly IPAs. Most over 6.5% ABV. ALL so taste & delicious. They know how to make beer. Got to meet one of the owners (and his lovely wife) while we were there. Passionate about his beer. Could have talked all afternoon long.

Highly recommend. We will be back...often.
14 CBs are on tap, served in a spacious indoor taproom where the staff takes exceptional care in maintaining glass cleanliness.

This was our favorite brewery we visiting during our trip! The “KOKUSHIBORI“ was amazing highly recommend! Our bartender Friday afternoon was very sweet and provided some great recommendations. The Test has been added to our must go list anytime we are in the area!
Staff and selection are the best!! Most unique sours and IPAs in NYC. Love coming here.
The taproom was a great space, and beautiful view. Enjoyed seeing the brew system right there as well! Beers were good and the pizza is ordered through QR code

OG OH! The best selection of collaborations and fancy guest beers (including from my town, Austin, recently). Plenty of to-go, although they don't keep it out where you can window shop. Decent merchandise selection. Smaller than other OH locations I've visited, but similarly cool vibe.

The place gets crowded on the evening hours. The brews are top notch and tend to rotate with the seasons.

The microbrewery is not far from bus & subway lines which makes it rather easy to get to.

We have been a loyal patron of this neighborhood gem for 4 years, and it never disappoints! The atmosphere is always lively, and the staff is incredibly friendly and knowledgeable about their impressive beer selection.

The seasonal menu keeps things fresh, and this visit didn't disappoint. Standouts included the Sonic Architecture (Hazy IPA), Artifact Engine (Dark Lager), and Infernal Optimism (Smoked Porter). I love that they offer various pour sizes, perfect for sampling new brews.

No food on site, but outside eats are welcome. Plus, daily events like trivia and jazz nights keep the crowd engaged. A true community hub!
FANTASTIC private party space. And friendly people, great beer, and wonderful vibes to go with it!

placeAddress: 5 Green Acres Rd W, Valley Stream, NY 11581
reviewText:
This restaurant is hands down the best restaurant at Green Acres commons! They have happy hour specials everyday that are unbeatable, and the food? Absolutely amazing. The spinach dip is perfection. The guac with fresh fried tortilla chips is delicious. The deep-dish pizza? Next level! I’m obsessed with their deep dish and flat bread pizzas. But let’s talk about the real star, the CLAM CHOWDER. It’s literally the BEST I’ve ever had in my life!

The bartenders know their craft, the cooks deliver incredible flavors, and the servers are top-notch. The management team at this location is exceptional, always ensuring a great experience.

Huge shoutout to Joey V, Andrew, and the entire crew for consistently delivering amazing food and service! We apprciate how you served our group and the attention to detail you always provide. Thank you!

placeAddress: 5 Green Acres Rd W, Valley Stream, NY 11581
reviewText: I love this restaurant! This is my spot. The happy hour specials are the best. Spinach dip is amazing, Guac and fresh torilla chips ...amazing...deep dish pizza ...amazing (I love the chicken , spinach, and brocolli pizza with white alfredo sauce...YUM). Cheesesticks...but OMG The CLAM CHOWDER is literally THE BEST! You will not find better even in a 3-star Michelin restaurant in my opinion. The bartenders there just know what they are doing. The cooks there just know how to cook. The servers are amazing as well. Management at this location is just awesome. They accommodate large groups as well in their back area if someone wanted to hold a party. Thank you Joey V, Andrew and the crew for being consistent with food quality and service 10+ Stars...Oh how could I forget about desert!!!! Mind blowing...best 700 calories of my life :)

placeAddress: 5 Green Acres Rd W, Valley Stream, NY 11581
reviewText:
Anyone who knows me, knows I state exactly what it is, for what it is!
Let me begin, with the service. The service was exceptional, beyond marks. I was greeted upon entering, and the server was at my table within 2 minute. The drinks. Everywhere I’ve been, including Applebees and Chilis, has developed a reputation of serving water whipped drinks. I mean who wants to pay $20+ for colored water? I know I don’t. This drink made me sit back upon first sip. The root beer (which BJ’s makes their own), was chilled, sweet, not too sweet, and delicious. Now, I had the full rack of ribs, broccoli, and white cheddar potatoes. When I tell you I had NO room for dessert. None! Though joining BJ’s gets you a free pizookie. The picture is worth smashing. However, you get it after 24 hours. Good thing,  because I had no room for anything! Management was very pleasant and reserved; respectful. The staff was courteous and welcoming. This has been my absolute best dining experience in New York, and I’ve been here 7 years. Kudos to you BJ’s in Valley Stream. Anyone who reads this, I’m a real person. A working Black American, who works as a Nurse and Business Owner, which gets it just like the next person. When I say, this is your place to visit. Definitely worth the drive (I live in the Bx). Believe that and that’s a check that’s guaranteed!

placeAddress: 5 Green Acres Rd W, Valley Stream, NY 11581
reviewText: I had a great experience at BJ’s Restaurant! The atmosphere was welcoming, and the service was friendly and attentive. The menu had a wide variety of options, from delicious steaks and seafood to their signature deep-dish pizzas. Everything we ordered was fresh and flavorful, and the portions were generous. Their house brews were a nice touch, offering a great selection to pair with the meal. It’s a great spot for a casual night out with friends or family. I’d definitely return for another visit!

placeAddress: 5 Green Acres Rd W, Valley Stream, NY 11581
reviewText:
Fell in love once I walked in.
Alba, is a shining star. Her energy brought smiles to our table . Why the four stars?
I do believe that service was slightly slower than I’d like, especially if you’re just waiting for napkins or plates. Those items should
be readily available. We ordered wings and a shareable pizza. The wings came in at lightening speed and the pizza came in about 15 mins after that. We asked for the “BJ’s Favorite” without meatballs, but we received a vegetarian deep dish instead. In addition, the pizza was room temp. We advised Alba of this, and she immediately spoke with the manager. The “new” pizza took about 15 mins and this time it was hot, fresh and most importantly, correct.

I don’t blame Alba for this error, but maybe there was a miscommunication in the kitchen as I heard the table behind us experience the same issue.

We will definitely be returning, and I look forward to the improvements that my review may possibly bring.

placeAddress: 5 Green Acres Rd W, Valley Stream, NY 11581
reviewText: I love this place and the servers are all great. I think the atmosphere here when I came for the Super Bowl was such a cool experience I wouldn’t have had anywhere else!

My experience here has never been worse. I put in a mobile order way in advance to my arrival. I got there at 5:30 and didn’t leave until 6:16. I spoke to a worker, Julia, who gave me a nasty attitude after I politely asked her when my drink would be ready, since at the time I was scheduled to board in 10 minutes. She told me, “Well if you don’t see it then it’s not ready.” She then started talking about me to her other coworkers saying, “This girl in the front thinks i’m a receptionist, people are already trying to talk to me.” I overheard other people who were waiting for their drinks talking about how rude she was being to them as well. Julia was overall rude, disrespectful, and very unprofessional.

placeAddress: 157-41 Cross Bay Blvd, Howard Beach, NY 11414
reviewText:
It's in my opinion that just about every Starbucks location is very busy. This one is no exception. I'm a local and this spot is jumping from open to close every day. Small parking lot so a lot of double parked cars all the time. On the other hand, the staff is pretty friendly and I've never received a wrong order. Perhaps just a missing packet of sriracha or something like that. I'd say the worst part of visiting here is running the risk of bumping into people you know lol Overall, they manage the madness. Kudos.

3/15/25
I was enticed to try the new grilled mozzarella and cheddar cheese on sourdough. I like that you can order packets of hot sauce with this grilled cheese and that they actually fulfill your customization. I requested a packet of each hot sauce so I could try the truff selections they recently added. They made my coffee very well today. I will say, while this grilled cheese is not bad, it's also nothing special. It's not $7.45 special at all. I'm left with the feeling that I should have just ordered the egg white and spinach wrap. There's more to it, and it's reasonably priced in comparison. Was the grilled cheese worth a try, yes. Will I ever again, no. Make your own at home...

placeAddress: Terminal 5, 6 Central Terminal Area, Jamaica, NY 11430
reviewText:
I've been here twice now. The first time, I had a really good experience. The second visit (last night) got both my boyfriend and I VERY sick. We ordered the calamari for an appetizer, chicken caesar salad, rigatoni with meatballs for our entrees and broccoli rabe for the side. The bread that they put on the table was bitter. Calamari was okay, the sauce was good. When we received our entrees, that's when things hit the fan. The Chicken Caesar was NOT fresh. There was also NO Caesar dressing. It was some lemon nonsense and the chicken was not fresh. The whole thing was the most horrible salad we've ever had. The rigatoni with meatballs wouldn't have been bad but the sauce was terribly sour and smokey and left a horrible aftertaste. We paid over $100 for our meal. The salad got sent back and I thought I could deal with the pasta but after taking it home and trying it again an hour later, that dish also went into the garbage. Service is also slow although our waitress was nice. My boyfriend ended up throwing up all night because of the food and I was so nauseous. Neither one of us have eaten since last night because of the nausea and it has been 18 hours since our meal at The Paris Café.

TLDR: Got food poisoning, food is not edible and comes with a bad aftertaste (if you can even stomach it),

Omg soooooo good! The sushi is top-tier—fresh, flavorful, and honestly some of the best around. They’ve also got this giant TV screen that is literally wall to wall, which perfect for catching a game. The cocktails are bomb too! GET. THE. LYCHEE. MARTINI. So freaking good and not too sweet. Plus, the staff is super chill and friendly, always checking in without being too much. My date and I had a really good time and we will be definitely coming back! (This just might be our spot from now on 🥰) Highly recommend, 10/10!!!

Hands down my favorite place for sushi ever. Everything is always super fresh and incredibly tasty. The staff are also super friendly and attentive, which just makes the experience that much better. King lobster roll and lychee martini is the perfect combo if you are feeling a little fancy

I came here today with my family for my cousin’s birthday and we had an absolute blast! Everything was super fresh and the staff were incredibly friendly and attentive! They sat us in one of those big booths in the back by the giant tv screens and let us put on the game that was going on tonight. Literally front row seats while enjoying amazing food! 😂😂😂 They have a great selection of Asian foods (sushi, teriyaki, hibachi, seafood boil, bubble tea) and an awesome bar with literally every kind of alcohol you can think of (I think I spotted the top shelf johnny walker blue label too 😮). My favorites from today were the rock shrimp, spicy kani salad, filet mignon carpaccio, spicy tuna roll, king lobster roll, chicken hibachi, and the scorpion bowl. That drink literally came with a flame on it! We had so much food but these were literally chef’s kiss. Overall it was a solid 100/10 experience and I will definitely be coming back to try everything on their menu! I saw another table get the seafood boil and it smelled absolutely amazing. Definitely starting with that next time!

Last night I went to one of the best Greek restaurant in Queens "Nick's Bistro" located at 104-20 Metropolitan Ave, Flushing, NY, Nick's Bistro is a delightful gem that offers a warm, inviting atmosphere coupled with exceptional cuisine. From the moment you step inside, the friendly staff ensures you feel welcomed, making it an ideal place for a casual meal or a special occasion. One standout dish at Nick's Bistro is their "Lemon Ouzo Chicken". This entrée features sautéed chicken breast in a luscious lemon ouzo sauce that is nothing short of amazing. The chicken is perfectly cooked, tender, and juicy, while the sauce provides a vibrant burst of citrus flavor with a subtle hint of anise from the ouzo, creating a delightful balance that tantalizes your taste buds. It’s a unique offering that showcases the restaurant’s commitment to blending traditional recipes with a modern twist.In addition to the Lemon Ouzo Chicken, the rest of the menu is thoughtfully curated, featuring a variety of other Greek and Mediterranean-inspired dishes that are equally impressive. The ambiance is cozy and charming, making it a perfect spot for both families and couples alike. Overall, Nick's Bistro is a must-visit for anyone in the Forset hills,Flushing area. The combination of outstanding service, a warm setting, and dishes like the unforgettable Lemon Ouzo Chicken makes for an excellent dining experience. #nicksbistro #onlyinqueens #Greekfood

This is a late review: We had Thanksgiving dinner here, and while the atmosphere was as stunning as I remembered from my first visit, the experience fell short in other areas.
The biggest disappointment was the service. Our server was polite but barely checked on us, and we constantly had to get his attention. Despite the restaurant being well-staffed, no one came by to refill our wine glasses, which is unacceptable at this price point.
The food was fine but not exceptional for the cost—I’ve had much better experiences elsewhere for far less. I tried their special Thanksgiving menu item—the roasted turkey breast with classic gravy and cranberry sauce—while my boyfriend had the filet bourguignon pappardelle. For dessert, we shared the green apple tarte tatin sundae—the portion was huge and perfect for two people.
The ambiance is definitely a strong point, with nice decor and dim lighting. However, our candle went out three times, which was a small but noticeable inconvenience.
Overall, while the setting is lovely, the mediocre food and inattentive service don’t justify the high prices. I expected more and, unfortunately, left feeling disappointed.

placeName: Other Half Brewing - Rockefeller Center Taproom
reviewText:
Other Half's taproom is a no-brainer, must-visit for craft beer lovers in New York. This brewery is known for its innovative and tasty hazy IPAs, but also stouts and sours. The tap list changes regularly, so there is always something new to discover, from exclusive releases to beloved classics. Recommended (February 28, 2025) is the Triple Citra Daydream and the BA Banaverse.

The atmosphere in the taproom is modern and relaxed, with limited seating space. You can taste beers in different sizes of glasses, so you can try multiple styles (beerflight available). The staff is friendly and knowledgeable and is happy to help you choose between all the IPA options.

In addition to the draft beers, there are also cans and bottles to go, including limited editions, ideal for further enjoyment at home. Whether you're a seasoned beer connoisseur or just want to try something new, Other Half offers a top experience. An absolute must for craft beer fans in NYC!

reviewText: The service staff are friendly and professional! The food is delicious and I love the interior design and dining atmosphere!

I come here about once a month and usually have great things to say. Today was a total miss. We ordered the hamachi crudo—the fish tasted totally off. We asked the server to take the mostly full plate back. They ended up charging us for it and didn’t follow up with us when the check was left at our table.

Le Boulangerie de Francoise is a true gem, a testament to the art of artisanal baking. Stepping inside, you're immediately enveloped in the warm, inviting aroma of freshly baked bread, a sensory delight that promises something truly special. Yes, the prices may be a touch higher than your average supermarket loaf, but the difference in quality is undeniable. Each handmade bread is a masterpiece, crafted with care and bursting with flavor that simply cannot be replicated.
My personal favorite? The Multigrain and Caraway seed bread. The hearty texture, the satisfying chew, and the unique, earthy notes of caraway make it an absolute delight. It's the kind of bread that elevates any meal, whether it's a simple sandwich or a side to a gourmet dinner.
And let's talk about the éclairs. Oh, the éclairs! They are simply divine. Each one is a perfect balance of delicate pastry, rich cream, and decadent glaze. What truly sets them apart is their freshness; every single one tastes as if it was just made moments ago. They are, without a doubt, the best éclairs I've ever had.
While the prices for the breads might initially raise an eyebrow, the exceptional quality and taste more than justify the cost. You're not just buying bread; you're investing in a culinary experience, a taste of authentic, handcrafted goodness. Le Boulangerie de Francoise is a must-visit for any bread lover, and the éclairs alone are worth the trip. Highly recommended!

Fantastic French Bakery in Bayside!

French Workshop Bakery in Bayside is an absolute gem! Their chocolate croissant is the best I’ve ever had—perfectly flaky, buttery, and rich in chocolate flavor. My teenager loves the ham and Swiss baguette, which is always fresh and satisfying. The Italian sandwich is my go-to, and it never disappoints.

For a sweet treat, my little girl enjoys their macarons, which are always fresh and delicious. The bakery itself is beautifully decorated, with elegant touches and a delicate floral arrangement—especially the red roses, which add a charming touch to the atmosphere.

Highly recommend this place for anyone looking for quality pastries and a cozy café experience!
Stop by here late after a long day for a quick coffee and dessert.  Pastries are always fresh!
Great bakery with delicious breads and desserts. #Can’tstopwon’tstopgoingtothisbakery

What is the point of having wonderful French food if the restaurant is incapable of preparing it it for the customer correctly? I’ve come here twice — the first time I ordered the egg-white croissant, and the second time, the egg and cheese brioche — and each time my food was cold on the inside. I even asked them to warm it up more — and what happened? The croissant / brioche became almost burnt on the outside, but the egg / cheese was still cold on the inside! So this is not a one-time problem, it’s an ongoing issue. Also, the staff is rushed and distracted, and it seems that they want to get the food moving “out the door” as quickly as possible, so proper time is not spent warming it up. Beautiful food that looks nice is wonderful, but if not prepared and served correctly, it’s not really very good at all, is it?

I'm not usually a fan of gourmet food like this, but I must say their chef is really good! Cheeseburger and southwest chicken salad are all delicious! The beer tastes great too!

Really a great local bar.  You'll end up chatting it up with someone....  The beers on top are primo.  They have some really good KCBC's on tap.  I've been to this bar three times since moving to NYC, and the bar tenders are always extremely kind and attentive.  Adrian is an absolute gentleman.  Great guy.
This bar has a juke box and plenty of TV screens for watching a game.  It's right on Austin street next to some good restaurants in case you get hungry and don't want bar food.  However, Tap House he's some very good food.

This place is the right amount of everything without ever being Too much.  Staff is lovely.  Drinks are flowing.  The food options appear to be fried, based on what we ordered but they had chicken wings, chicken tenders, fries, waffle fries, tots, and mozzarella sticks, so the main food groups were covered.  Good mix and crowd of people. Plenty of TVs for watching sports or 'sportsball' depending on your familiarity.

I came here on a Tuesday night, after trying another place first. Beer from the tap was a bit flat. I wish the bartender would have greeted us like he greeted others when they walked in. Definitely a local spot with folks that must come regularly. The boneless wings and waffle fries were okay. I don't think we will try again.
Great food and Irish Pub, you can't go wrong!!!

reviewText: The Westbury didn't disappoint with great service, a good selection of Irish drinks available and the food was great. Atmosphere was excellent too.

estbury is amazing! I’m a recent transplant from Bunratty, and I can tell you with 100% certainty that The Guinness at the Westbury is top-notch! And the entire staff is fantastic at pulling a solid pint of Guinness.

Alana Is an absolute princess behind the bar… She’s educated, intelligent, friendly, and super sociable! On top of all that that she can pull a fantastic pint of a Guinness. The manager Norman was also very helpful, and he suggested the slow cooked beef brisket French dip, and it was unbelievable. It’s rare when you can observe a staff follow, respect, and joke around with their leader all at the same time… but that’s Norman’s way…

The other Floor Manager is John, who at times sports a true blue Tom Sellick mustach, and other times, clean shaves everything to appear as a a college undergrad barback. But John leads from the front and hunks in whoever his team needs a hand. Finally, Sophie is a wonderful addition to the team, she may not know where Bunratty is, but she’s a sweet soul with a bubbling personality. Also knows how to pull a perfect Guinness. The short rib French dip is delicious! This place is a 10/10!

(I also can tell you that AJ and Malia are fantastic! But John made me replace that review. I’ll remove this part when his texts me to change it)
I ordered some Sweet Potato Fries and they were raw & rubbery but Maybe the Vietnamese food is better- I was just starving & only ordered the fries but they were Unfortunately horrible, sorry.
Wonderful staff

Excellent

Classic margaritas are delicious must have for appetizers I had buffalo chicken wings with blue cheese 10/10 buffalo sauce delicious blue cheese it's not over power cheese burger was well done sweet potato are delicious must have Philly cheese steak sandwich on the panini it's was okay 3/10 mozzarella sticks were good 9/10 monster steak nachos,9/10

I went here to celebrate my 30th birthday tonight and service was horrible. The drinks we got were good. I got fish and chips, which I have to admit was good. One of my friends got a Reuben and ceaser salad, which the ceaser was too sweet and they kindly swapped to fries. My other friend, who is a tiny woman asked if she could get a kids pot pie and was denied because you have to be 12 and under. Okay fine I can understand that but then when she got her adult pot pie, the chicken was giant chunks and extremely dry. The server stopped at the table maybe three times and never stayed long enough for us to even say something about the food. And when I got the bill there was automatic gratuity and a charge if you use a card. When I explained I was going to tip in cash I was met with attitude. I was also uninformed I had to go up to the register to pay with a physical card because the QR code only offered Google pay and nothing else. The only positive thing was getting our photos taken in a HIMYM fashion.
Looks good. Delicious 😋. Nice people.
Loved the food. I had a good time, my 1st in an actual pub. I got a chance to celebrate part of my heritage. Very friendly
Do you like HIMYM? Then you have to try drinks they have🥰

We went because it’s the HIMYM bar. Cool place with 3 floors and plenty of drink/food options. Large draft beer list as well, and pretty good cocktail menu. A good place to grab a seat and have a couple of drinks if you’re in the area. Easy walking distance from Times Square and Central Park
If you’re a HIMYM fan then it’s a must stop, with the special cocktail menu and merch all over the walls.

A iconic place, where I had many great memories from the series. However, it was one of the worst table services I have ever experienced. It’s really sad to see such a special place turn into a big regret.

I made a reservation for 730 last night (St. Patrick’s Day, so I knew it would be busy, and we were prepared to be patient!). We were there before 730 & were seated around 742. We ordered some Guinness and some food, which came very quickly. At 8:43, after we had finished our food and were nearing the end of our first round, the waitress asked if we wanted more to eat. We asked if we could have a second to decide if we wanted another round of beers. She said “No… if you want to drink, there’s the bar. We have a long line of reservations to get to tonight.” we had purposely booked a table so that we could be together and chat as part of our group were visitors from out of town. Only having the table for an hour seems really unfair. Our waitress barely checked in on us, and then when we asked for just one separate check (so a visitor could expense her dinner to her company since she was in town for work), she said absolutely not. We don’t do itemized receipts. (I was holding an itemized receipt in my hand as she said this.) All of this information would have been totally fine if our waitress had simply communicated with us in a kind way, but she was very stressed and seemed to almost be yelling at us throughout the night. Very disappointed in Mcgee’s this time.

Fun place to visit for the drinks and for the How I Met your Mother references, which is what attracts the very touristy clientele. Service is efficient but slow and not overly friendly. Food is ok - nothing to write home about.
lovely Irish pub, will have to drop in again for a bite to eat

Irish pub, complete menu but total surcharge, as a fan of the series I was a little disappointed

Unfortunately, I was a little disappointed. Anyone who knows and enjoys watching the series “How I Met Your Mother” knows what McGee’s looks like on the inside. Unfortunately it's not like in the series.

The food was good and the staff was nice.

Went here for a few drinks. Were received very unfriendly and seated directly at the door, even though there was a better place available. When we asked, we were not implemented either. Drinks came quickly, but the Naked Man, for example, only tasted like pure alcohol. The waitress only tried to be friendly when it came to the bill, which already included a 20% tip as a “gratitude”. The appearance of the pub is only slightly reminiscent of the bar in How I Met Your Mother. Overall not recommended.

If HIMYM has left its mark on you, a beer at McGee's is worth marking in your diary! Historic Irish-style pub that inspired the historic venue of the famous sitcom. Be careful, don't expect the set of How I Met, which is indeed a set, but having said that, the atmosphere remains peppered with photos, dishes and cocktails dedicated to the beloved characters. Don't miss it! Perhaps preferable during less crowded times to be able to enjoy the refined setting with due tranquility. Costs? Well, we are between Central Park and Times Square.....
My favorite place ❤️
Incredible food with great service! Lovely Irish pub with not too far a walk from Times Square. So many HIMYM references which I loved!

reviewText: Great food.  Weird vibes.  Typically has some riff raff hanging around.  Staff is friendly-- attentive service. Food is fresh, so you'll wait longer than at the average "fast food" joint. Despite the awesome food, I patronize as a last resort because I don't like waitimg around in the atmosphere.  Always take out my order.  Food is worth the price you pay.

A gem for weddings and celebrations in Brooklyn. A beautiful venue for photos, caring and professional staff and wonderful culinary team. My couples have loved every bit of their experience at Brooklyn Winery.
They do a Wine tasting, if you go, do it with Jamen. He was AMAZING. Fun, engaging, funny, SO knowledgeable. Thanks to him I had an "ah-ha" moment and now know what wine I like. Def recommend 100000%

I had an amazing time on the wine tour & tasting with Jamen at Brooklyn Winery! He was incredibly knowledgeable and kept the group engaged throughout the entire experience. Highly recommend this tour for anyone looking to learn more about wine in a fun and relaxed setting!

Hollywood Smile Photo Booth review :
I had the pleasure of returning to one of my favorite venues, and it once again exceeded my expectations! The staff is incredibly professional and kind, ensuring everything runs smoothly. The food is absolutely delicious, making every bite a delight. The lively interior adds a wonderful ambiance that enhances the overall experience.

Everyone  loved the addition of the photo booth at the wedding—it was a fantastic way to capture memories and bring guests together.
Delicious & full of flavor & the staff was super friendly! I highly recommend.
I’ve never satiated lust through quivering cream but the man in the back has the supply and I’m in demand.

Bought this “dubai chocolate strawberries” today and was very very disappointed ☹️ it costs 20$ and you get few strawberries drizzled with a little (very little) bit of a green chocolate (it doesn’t taste like pistachio at all so probably just a colored white chocolate), 3 pistachios and kataifi that was just on top(not more than what you see on the picture). It is embarrassing to sell this to customers for 20$ and call it a thing. they also have a 10$ strawberries covered by regular chocolate which i got before and they were actually covered, so I don’t understand why there is such a big price difference and I get what i get. Just very disappointing. (No complaints about crapes)

We passed by after an evening at the bar and wanted to eat something light but chocolatey. It definitely hit the mark. Very fast service. For my personal taste, as a food lover, the chocolate took over and I didn't taste the crepe. We took one with strawberries and one without. In my opinion, it would have been possible to cut the strawberries into smaller pieces so that I could eat a strawberry with every bite. The guy at the counter was very nice and smiling
The presentation could be much more impressive. We received it in an aluminum mold. I think it would have been much more successful in a branded carton.

A huge selection of awesome crepes to try and every one I’ve had is perfect. They’re always fresh and absolutely delicious. My favorite is “The Famous”. It’s a huge crepe loaded with strawberries, banana, chocolate, and nutella topped with whipped cream and vanilla ice cream. Yummy!
The sandwiches here are always good. prices are just below the average deli cost.

I’m CPR certified and know how to treat a choking victim so I excused myself from the table and gave myself chest blows in the restroom while forcefully coughing. Finally the bay leaf came up. It was a terrifying experience and the leaf scratched the inside of my throat. I explained what happened to our server but I don’t think she fully understood what I was saying and I probably wasn’t super coherent. Bay leaves are a known choking hazard and are toxic if ingested. If a restaurant is going to use bay leaves in the cooking process then they should be removed before the dish is served.

“An absolute gem! From the moment we walked in, the ambiance was warm and inviting. The staff was incredibly attentive, making sure we had everything we needed without being intrusive. Now, the food—simply outstanding! Every dish was packed with flavor, beautifully presented, and clearly made with high-quality ingredients. The chef’s attention to detail truly shined through. We especially loved Haleem, which was cooked to perfection. The entire dining experience was top-notch, and we can’t wait to return. Highly recommended!”

The aroma of the dish was intoxicating, hinting at the rich flavors within.  The ingredients were clearly of the highest quality, meticulously chosen for their unique characteristics.  Each bite was a symphony of textures and tastes, a testament to the chef's skill.  While the price may be considered high, the experience was truly exceptional. It was a meal to be savored and remembered.

The goat biryani was really good! A good portion for a good price and good quantity of meat.

I also had their Ramadan special Haleem. It was the closest to the authentic Hyderabadi Haleem amongst the 5-6 places I have tried in this country.

Made the long drive worth it!

I  highly recommend this place! The biryani had an authentic Hyderabadi flavor, with an amazing taste and perfectly tender, juicy meat. The haleem was fantastic as well. If you’re looking for a true Hyderabadi culinary experience, this is the place to be!

As a Hyderabadi myself in a whole new country i miss biryani pretty much all the time but , when i ordered from this place thinking its just another biryani spot with the name Hyderabad i was amazed when the food arrived it looked just like back home with amazing aroma and the same exact taste!! Took me back home for a while. Put me on the list as a regular!

The goat biryani was so good and the side of curry/salan with yogurt was also very good… I ordered four days in a row from my son Armann’s DoorDash account… that side of salan reminded me of Hyderabad..

164-26 Cross Bay Blvd, Howard Beach, NY 11414
reviewText:
This is a review for a visit on Friday, 2/21/25. We arrived just after 12pm. We were seated promptly. We waited a bit for menus. 10-15 minutes after ordering we got up, cancelled our order, and left.

What I am about to describe is from my observations while being there for 30-35 minutes, and we never even received our drink order, which was two regular coffees and a water. The only staff seen was one server, a lady with glasses, and a busboy. This was the scenario:

- There were two people seated at the counter, by the wall. They already had their food. I do not know if they were still eating or finished. At some point, one of them had to approach the staff to get their check and pay.

- There was a group (family?), with kids, seated by the wall where the piano is located. I thought they were waiting for their check. Apparently this family had already placed their order before we arrived. They were just receiving their drink order when we decided to get up and leave.

- There was a group (family?), adults and teens, already finished eating waiting for their check. Someone from the table had to approach the staff to get their check.

- There was a couple sitting at the table facing outside. They already had their food and the food looked about halfway eaten. The male kept looking back towards the counter. I am assuming they wanted the check. No one checked in with them during the time we were there.

- Behind the couple was an empty table with dishes. This table was attended to by a busboy 20 minutes into our seating.

- There were two ladies seated by the other wall, opposite the piano, by the window. They already had eaten their food. One of the ladies had to approach the staff to let them know she wanted another drink and the check.

- There was a group of three ladies two tables away from the window by the wall opposite the piano. They had already eaten and wanted to order dessert. They had to flag the server for their dessert order after our order was taken. The ladies received their dessert order before we left.

- Two ladies walked in and approached the counter to be seated. The lady with the glasses remained by the counter and pointed to where the two ladies could sit.

Other than what was described above, there were no other customers to attend to. During our time sitting and waiting, no orders were taken, and no food was brought out. The lady with the glasses looked shocked when we were leaving and told to cancel the order. She didn't ask why. On her own, she said it hasn't been that long.

One of the ladies seated next to us said she was sorry we were leaving, that the food was very good. While the food may be very good, the service was very poor.

For a service and customer oriented business, I would say no matter how good the food is, it is definitely not worth the lack of service. While the pricing is a little on the high side, it was definitely going to be a treat to dine at Nana's.

I would say that while the Howard Beach and Ozone Park communities are trying to support Nana's, if things don't change, Nana's won't be around much longer. There seems to be a lack of reviews. Reviews help people make decisions.

placeAddress: Retail Market, 2344 Arthur Ave, Bronx, NY 10458
reviewText:
I was looking for an Italian sandwich place and this one came up on Google Mike's Deli. When I got there I was greeted with a menu then I went ahead and ordered a pastrami roll with a Coke as I waited I was asked whether I wanted to pay cash or credit when I asked how much it was it was $20 I think with everything going on and these local businesses rising prices ridiculously high will drive the economy to the floor I would say stay away from this place consistent with high prices not too good of quality and overall bad experience.

Response to the owner:

I believe in fair pricing and good customer service. My comment about the prices was based on my personal experience, not an attack on your business. Instead of assuming bad intentions, a conversation would have been more productive. I wish you success, but respect goes both ways.
Supporting small businesses doesn’t mean blindly accepting high prices or dismissive service. I came in as a paying customer, not an adversary. Instead of engaging in a conversation, you assumed bad intentions and responded with hostility. A business thrives not just on quality ingredients but also on how it treats its customers. I hope you reflect on this, because respect and good service are just as important as the food you serve and by the way your pastrami isn't that good at all ...very dried and then overcooked.

placeAddress: Retail Market, 2344 Arthur Ave, Bronx, NY 10458
reviewText: I took my 92 year old father there today. He was born in Castrofilipo, Sicily.  He saw the tripe in the butcher showcase and asked me if they offered it for lunch. I went to Mike's counter and asked and they did. I ordered it for him and I tasted it. It was absolutely delicious. I ordered the eggplant sandwich that beat Bobby Flay, it was also delicious. Thank you for beating Bobby. I live on Long Island and  I can't wait to go back. My father loved the tripe. We ordered a takeout for him to have next week.

My husband got diagnosed with Celiac in late 2023 and has been trying to find good GF bread and baked goods since then. We found Sixteen Mill in early 2024 after trying all the commercially available options, farmers' markets, and most GF baked goods in NYC. Sixteen Mill is second to none. The bread and the treats are not just delicious for gluten free goods, they are delicious by any standard. We've introduced friends and family who are not GF to this bakery and they all cannot stop raving about it. The donut and cake textures are absolutely magical and the breads have become must have staples in our home. Everything is not only delicious but also made with the best organic ingredients, which is really important to us. This place is truly one of a kind and we're so lucky and happy it exists!

BEST GF VEGAN EVER! Talia and her team are true culinary magicians! I have been craving this texture and finally found it. I tried almost every single item that was available for purchase and have no notes. Thank you!

Rare and wonderful place for great variety of Belgian beer (~8 kinds on tap and many more in bottles/ cans), ~6 styles of mussels, plus hearty steak frites, etc. in a laidback atmosphere with attentive and friendly service.

Prices are not cheap, but an evening at BXL is like an evening in Europe without having to fly there!

Beers are about $14, 2 lbs of mussels cost $28. They have an all you can eat mussel special on Sunday and Monday that I have made a mental note to go back for sometime — Yum!

This time I had my mussels marinière style, with white wine and shallots, which was delicious and light. Upon request, they brought some delicious baguette to soak into the broth.

Last time I had the mussels grande-mère style with cream and bacon, which was equally delicious, but definitely more filling.

My partner had the steak frites, which was definitely a nice portion, and cooked to perfection.

We were tempted by the waffle for dessert, but just did not have the room, especially after a Duvel or two!

This place is truly a neighborhood gem. I highly recommend going and exploring the delights of Belgian food in this gentle and enjoyable atmosphere.

Good Afternoon,

I am writing this review to formally address the unacceptable and discriminatory experience my party encountered at your establishment. From the moment we arrived, the visit was plagued with poor service, lack of communication, and blatant disregard for inclusivity.

Our experience began with a phone reservation that, upon arrival, could not be found. Despite this, we were assured that our party of five would be seated within 25 to 30 minutes at most. As my brother uses a wheelchair, we opted to wait in the lobby near the check-in booth to minimize unnecessary movement. However, an hour and 20 minutes passed without any update from staff.

Concerned about the delay, my mother approached an employee named Takia to inquire about our wait time. She dismissively responded, “Well, your party has a wheelchair, so y’all have to wait.” This statement was not only unprofessional but also deeply concerning. When my mother asked for clarification, Takia explained that we required a “special table” to avoid blocking the pathway. If this was a known requirement, why were we not informed upon arrival, after 30 minutes, or even after an hour? Instead, we had to proactively ask, only to be met with indifference.

At this point, another employee, Davina, joined the conversation. As Takia briefed her on the situation, Davina repeatedly referred to my brother as the “wheelchair person” rather than using his name, which had been provided upon check-in. This dehumanizing language is unacceptable and discriminatory.

After waiting an additional 30 minutes, we inquired again about our seating, at which point Davina responded with a dismissive attitude, raising her voice and insisting that we should have communicated differently upon arrival. At our request, a manager named Patricia intervened and finally seated us—after nearly two hours of waiting. To our disbelief, the seating arrangement required no special accommodations beyond standard accessibility, proving that the excessive wait time was unwarranted.

To make matters worse, Davina continued to exhibit unprofessional behavior, intentionally walking past our table while audibly sighing and making snide remarks. She even pointed out our table to a male colleague, saying, “This is them,” followed by laughter.

No person—regardless of ability—deserves to be subjected to such treatment. Whether dining at a high-end steakhouse or a casual restaurant, all guests should be treated with dignity and respect. This experience was discriminatory, unacceptable, and will not go unaddressed. I intend to escalate this matter to the fullest extent to ensure accountability and justice for my brother.

I expect a prompt response outlining how this situation will be rectified and what actions will be taken to prevent such occurrences in the future.

placeAddress: JFK Access Rd Terminal 4, Retail Hall - West, JFK International Airport, Jamaica, NY 11430
reviewText:
La peor atención al cliente que hemos recibido. Desde que llegas, la anfitriona parece que le molesta asignarte una mesa. Luego la camarera se demoró muchísimo en acercarse a tomar al pedido, aproximadamente esperamos 15 minutos. En traer el pedido fue peor, ni siquiera pudo traer las bebidas (que no se preparan: cervezas y una gaseosa). Apenas terminamos de comer trajo la cuenta sin habérsela pedido y tuvimos que pagarle rápidamente porque claramente estuvo encima nuestro esperando el pago. Luego pedimos una cerveza adicional a otro camarero, trajo la cerveza e inmediatamente regresó a la
Mesa con la cuenta y dijo que debíamos de pagarla. Luego de unos minutos (luego de pagar)  regresó y nos desarmó la mesa, de una manera arbitraria y sin dar razones. Le pedimos que llame a su supervisor y de una manera grosera nos dijo que era lo que había pasado, que cuál era el problema, en todo momento estuvo agresivo, no quería llamar al supervisor. Finalmente el manager se acercó a la mesa (luego de 20 minutos), nos escuchó con mucha atención y nos pidió disculpas, además nos dijo que hablaría con el personal porque la atención al cliente es lo que quieren resaltar en el restaurante. Decidir por este restaurante terminó siendo una experiencia HORRIBLE.
reviewTitle: Pésima atencion al cliente, no vayan
